record.title: ADJOURNMENT UNTIL 10 A.M. TOMORROW
record.narrative:
ADJOURNMENT UNTIL 10 A.M. TOMORROW -- (Senate - October 29, 2007)

[Page: S13529]

speaking.paragraph: Madam President, if there is no further business, I ask unanimous consent that the Senate stand adjourned under the previous order.

record.narrative: There being no objection, the Senate, at 7:19 p.m., adjourned until Tuesday, October 30, 2007, at 10 a.m.
